Release.Comments

A selection of tracks from this years Hottest 100!

Now in its 22nd year, triple j once again provided the
soundtrack to Australia Day, counting down the best songs of
2014 in another massive Hottest 100. A record 2,099,707 votes
were cast by 258,762 music fans from 188 different countries,
making triple j's Hottest 100 the world's biggest music poll.

A number of Australian artists were strong contenders for the
top spot, but in the end it was independent Melbourne musician
Chet Faker's track "Talk Is Cheap" which received the most votes
from triple j listeners.

The Hottest 100 wraps up another huge year in music, which saw
some incredible talent and brand new sounds introduced to the
world, as well as some old favourites come back to dominate the
airwaves.

This year's double album features songs from Chet Faker, Hilltop
Hoods, Sia, Asgeir, Peking Duk, Mark Ronson, and many more.
